node.text:
"If we didn't have bees to do pollination, we'd only be eating wheat and rice." 🐝

Research assistant Rui Gonçalves of the Oxford Bee Lab is studying bee nutrition to ensure UK bee populations can grow.

Discover why Rui's role is one of #101Jobs that change the world ⬇️
https://www.ukri.org/our-work/101-jobs-that-change-the-world/

#TruePlanet #Oxford #OxfordUni #OxfordUniversity #Bees #Beekeeping #BeesNeedsWeek

node.title: Beekeeping is in the top 101 jobs that change the world

node.text:
Today is #DontStepOnABeeDay! 🐝
.
These busy pollinators need our help to take care of their environment! Over in @wytham_woods, teams of experts and volunteers are learning about bee behaviours and what they need to thrive.
.
Find out more ➡️ oxfordplanbee.web.ox.ac.uk
#Oxford #OxfordUni #OxfordUniversity #bee #bees #trueplanet

Smile for the camera! 📸 🐒 

A camera trap study by Prof David Macdonald at @OxfordZoology has captured 6 million images of over 250 species in South East Asia.

Now the study has turned into a downloadable game, teaching players about conservation efforts.

Here are some snaps of a Nicobar crab-eating macaque, a Malay weasel, a greater one-horned rhino, and the Shortridge's langur.
